trans-unit.source: "Preliminary" support as feature is still in development
"Rangy" Range library with old IE support
"Supported" refers to accessing the values using the dataset property. Current spec only refers to support on HTML elements, only some browsers also have support for SVG/MathML elements.
"Unknown" support for mobile browsers is due to lacking a method of tabbing through fields.
"online" does not always mean connection to the internet, it can also just mean connection to some network.
'animation-fill-mode' property is not supported in Android browser below 2.3.
- JavaScript execution time is limited to 10 seconds for each top-level entry point.
- The maximum size for a canvas element is 3 megapixels for devices with less than 256 MB RAM and 5 megapixels for devices with greater or equal than 256 MB RAM.
- The maximum size for decoded GIF, PNG, and TIFF images is 3 megapixels for devices with less than 256 MB RAM and 5 megapixels for devices with greater or equal than 256 MB RAM.
-moz-appearance:none doesn't remove the dropdown arrow in select tag
10up Open Sources IE 8 and 9 Support for Flexbox
